      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "const S = readline();\nconsole.log([...S.replace(/[^a-z]/ig, '')].map(c => c.charCodeAt(0)).filter((c, i) => c % 2 === (i + 1) % 2).reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0));",
      "statement": "Given an input string [[S]], add the ASCII codes of its <<letters>> if they meet the following condition:\n\nBoth the parity of the code and the position of the letter in [[S]] is the same. <<Ignore all non-letter characters (they do not count for the positions)!>>\n\nFor example in <<a2ce>> {{a}} is the first letter and its code is 97 so the parity is the same (odd). We ignore {{2}} (non-letter). The code of {{c}} is 99 but this is the 2nd letter so the parity differs therefore we skip it. Lastly the code of {{e}} is 101 and this is the 3rd letter so the parity is the same again. The result = 97 + 101 = 198\n\nYou must output the sum of the appropriate character codes.",
